#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:25
msgid ""
"The Origin of an Object is shown in the 3D view by a small orange circle. "
"This is highlighted in the image to the right by the red arrow. The origin "
"tells Blender *where that Object is in 3D space*. What you see in the 3D "
"view (vertices, edges etc) is what makes up the Object."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:30
msgid ""
"While the Origin is equivalent to the center of the *Object*, it does not "
"have to be located in the center of the *Mesh*. This means that an Object "
"can have its center located on one end of the mesh or even completely "
"outside the mesh. For example, the orange rectangle in the image has its "
"Origin located on the far left of the mesh."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:36
msgid "Now let's examine *Rotation around the individual origins*."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:39
msgid ""
"The blue rectangle has its Origin located in the center of the mesh, while "
"the orange rectangle has its Origin located on the left hand side."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:41
msgid ""
"When the Pivot Point is set to *Individual Origins*, the center of each "
"Object (indicated by the red arrow) remains in place while the Object "
"rotates around it in the path shown by the black arrow."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:47
msgid "In Edit mode"
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:49
msgid ""
"In Edit mode, setting the Pivot Point to Individual Origins produces "
"different results when the selection mode is set to Vertex, Edge or Face. "
"For example, Vertex mode produces results similar to setting the pivot point"
" to median and Edge mode often produces distorted results. Using Individual "
"Origins in Face mode produces the most predictable results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../manual/editors/3dview/transform/transform_control/pivot_point/individual_origins.rst:60
